# Dazzle

> Cloud stages for AI agents and live streaming.
> https://dazzle.fm

Dazzle gives you cloud stages — isolated browser environments that render and broadcast your content. Control everything from the `dazzle` CLI. Two stage tiers: GPU (NVIDIA RTX, hardware WebGL, 30 FPS shaders) and CPU (software OpenGL, lighter content).

## Docs

- [Content Authoring Guide](https://dazzle.fm/guide.md): Environment specs, page setup, performance tiers (GPU vs CPU), what works at 30 FPS, what to avoid, design tips for 720p streaming, persistence, live events.
- [Full LLM Reference](https://dazzle.fm/llms-full.txt): Complete getting started walkthrough, CLI reference, authentication, content guide, and typical workflow — all in one file.

## Quick Start

```bash
curl -sSL https://dazzle.fm/install.sh | sh   # install CLI
dazzle login                                    # authenticate
dazzle s new my-stage                           # create a stage
dazzle s up                                     # activate it
dazzle s sync ./my-app --watch                  # push content (auto-refresh)
dazzle s ss -o preview.png                      # screenshot to verify
```

## Stage Tiers

- **GPU stages**: NVIDIA RTX with hardware-accelerated WebGL and NVENC encoding. Shaders, raymarching, complex post-processing — all 30 FPS.
- **CPU stages**: Software-rendered OpenGL on shared CPU. CSS animations, Canvas 2D, DOM, WebGL geometry all 30 FPS. Fragment-heavy shaders limited.

